<!--- BEGIN INFO BAR --->	
<div class="INFO_BAR">
    <div class="left shifter">
        <%= image_tag "animated_icon.gif", id: "hint_orig" %>
	<%= image_tag "hint_collection.png", id: "hint_coll" %>
	<%= image_tag "hint_spotlight.png", id: "hint_spot" %>
	<%= image_tag "hint_explore.png", id: "hint_expl" %>
	<%= image_tag "hint_user.png", id: "hint_user" %>
    </div>
    <div class="expandable"><div class="info_text">
		<div class="hintbar_desc">
		<span id="orig">
		Curarium leverages the power of the crowd to annotate, curate, & augment works with the aim of constructing shareable, media-rich stories & elaborate arguments about individual items as well as groups of items.
		</span>
		<span id="coll">
		Collections:
		 Find and follow collections of interest to you OR ingest your own collection* of up to 30,000 records in just 5 minutes.
		</span>
		<span id="spot">
		Spotlights:
		 Tell stories by pulling directly from the content you’ve collected in your trays. 
		Publish, share, and export your spotlights. 
		</span>
		<span id="expl">
		Explore:
		 Within any collection, browse, filter, search, and generate visualizations.
			Annotate records and make additions to their metadata.
			Save individual records, groups of records, or visualizations to a tray. 
			Categorize what you save using as many trays as you need. 
		</span>
		<span id="user">
		You:
		Start or join user circles to share and collaborate on work within a specified collection or set of collections. 
		When you explore any collections in your circles, you can use a social tray to work in real time with circle members to collect and order records. 
		</span>
		</div>
    	
    	<div id="hintbar_links">
		<b><%= link_to "Learn more", '/about'%></b>
		</br><b><%= link_to "Sign Up",  new_user_path  %></b>, Join the Community
		</div>
		<div id="hintbar_search">
		<b><%= link_to "Search", '/about'%> <%= image_tag "search_r.png" %></b>		
		</div>
    
    </div></div>
 
</div><!--- END INFO BAR --->	

